reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The PERFECT bookshelves!
reviews.reviewText: These are amazing shelves! They look extremely high quality and are pretty straightforward to put together! Once you get some books on the sleeves they are very stable. Hold a ton of books and even more storage behind the doors! I will say that the cabinet shelving is a little shallow, but definitely not a deal breaker! I love these!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 7, 2023
reviews.reviewText: These bookcases were a dream to build. The instructions were very easy to follow and all the parts and pieces were nicely bagged and labeled, so it was easy to organize before building. I bought five and by the time I put the last one together it took me about 30 minutes. They fit nicely together to make a larger unit. I put them on the sides of a smaller shelving unit that holds our TV to create a large entertainment unit across an entire wall in our family room. I cut the base trim away and anchored these units flush against the wall and now have built in bookcases at a fraction of what it would have cost to build. They are very sturdy. The only complaint I have is that the screws that anchor the shelves show on the outside of the unit, so you need to buy plastic stickers to hide them. All in all we are quite pleased with how it turned out.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Lots of room and easy to build!
reviews.reviewText: My old bookshelf broke and this was the first (online) one I bought that seems like it’ll last, it’s a little wiggly given I couldn’t bolt it into the wall, because there’s a window there (but I’m sure with that added step it’d be a lot more stable). Only realized once I added all my books how little room I had left (to my own surprise, buying this I was sure 60+ books were a little too much for an Amazon shelf). I’ll definitely be looking into getting a second one when my collection grows, it was very easy to put together, given my lack of patience when it comes to building furniture, it was an hour or so job for me. I will say it is a bit messy out of the box, styrofoam bits and pieces, a little dusty too, a wipe down and sweep fixed it up nicely, just for warning. For the price though, I’d say it’s worth investing, it’s a solid bookshelf if you’re handy with tools.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Lots of space
reviews.reviewText: I was pleased with the overall function and look of these shelves. They have 4 evenly spaced shelves and 2 in the cabinets. Really like the doors, it broke up the the look of the shelves and the style of the door is nice. They are not difficult to put together, it just takes time. I added some shelf liner to kick them up a notch and installed the liner as I put the shelf together. The shelves are stationary and they are on the shallow side. Would definitely recommend!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Love this book shelf! It’s looks beautiful, and is really good quality. It was also easy to put together which I was nice.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Looks great but shallow with low shelves
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. These book cases are shallow and the shelf height is shorter than I expected and they cannot be adjusted. The wood is good material but the top half of the shelf shows the metal screws on the inside and make it look very cheap. They should have provided something to cover them. Also, the anchor brackets to prevent the bookshelf from falling over are too short. I have molding and 1/4 round on my walls so the brackets cannot reach the wall. You definitely need to anchor the book case, it's not very sturdy and may tip over. Overall, the price was a bit high for the quality but, paired with the table, makes them look high end.

reviews.reviewText: Great quality..clear instructions was easy to put it together

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Pretty. And you get what you pay for.
reviews.reviewText: And what did you pay for? A relatively cheap 6 shelf bookcase. It's not durable or strong but it fits my budget and looks pretty good.During set up I did have two issues. One of my screws broke -be careful and do not over tighten! Some of the doorknobs would not fit to the provided screw. The screw was not long enough to get the job done so I chipped at the hole on the inside of the door to get it to fit together. I bought two but this was only an issue for one of the cases. Strange.I actually just bought two more since I decided I needed more shelf space and am happy with appearance. Whoo.
